<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:
MHD_cleanup_connections invokes the user-supplied callback daemon->notify_connection. If that callback calls back into the library (for example calls MHD_stop_daemon on the same daemon), the following indirect call chain can occur: MHD_cleanup_connections -> daemon->notify_connection (user callback) -> MHD_stop_daemon -> close_all_connections -> MHD_cleanup_connections. This re-enters MHD_cleanup_connections (and close_all_connections) indirectly, causing recursion.
</scenario>
